{"id":"javelin","term":"Javelin","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(1.) Heb. hanith, a lance, from its flexibility (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Samuel 18:10\">1 Sam. 18:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:11\">11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 19:9\">19:9</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 19:10\">10</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 21:15\">20:33</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) Heb. romah, a lance for heavy-armed troops, so called from its piercing (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 25:7\">Num. 25:7</a>). (See ARMS.)</p>\n\u0000","refs":["1 Samuel 18:10","Genesis 1:11","Genesis 19:9","Genesis 19:10","Genesis 21:15","Numbers 25:7"]}